All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Coordenadas
Represents a coordinate point (x, y) on the grid.
Death_Event
Represents a "Death" event within the simulation.
Event
Represents a scheduled event within the simulation.
Event_Strategy
Defines the strategy interface for handling various events within the simulation.
EventFactory
A factory class for creating different types of Event objects.
Grid
Represents the grid environment for pathfinding, defined by its dimensions, obstacles, and special cost zones.
Individual
Represents an individual entity within the simulation that navigates a grid, can reproduce, and has a lifecycle defined by birth and death times.
Input_Parser
A utility class responsible for parsing simulation parameters from different sources, primarily from a text file or from command-line arguments (for random generation).
Main
The main entry point for the simulation application.
Move_Event
Implements the Event_Strategy for a "Move" event.
PEC
Represents the Priority Event Calendar (PEC) for the simulation.
PopulationManager
Manages the population of Individual entities within the simulation.
RandomUtil
A utility class providing methods for generating various types of random numbers.
Reproduction_Event
Implements the Event_Strategy for a "Reproduction" event.
Simulation
Manages and executes the simulation process.
Simulation_Context
Represents the central context for the simulation, holding references to all major components and shared simulation state.
SimulationParameters
A data class that encapsulates all the parameters required to configure and run a simulation.
Special_Cost_Zone
Represents a special cost zone within the grid.
